    "faq_8XYCd7": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question_kkQ9cg": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How accurate is the Arccos Smart Laser Rangefinder?",
            "text": "<p>The Arccos Smart Laser Rangefinder is accurate to within ±1 yard.</p><p>It delivers precise line-of-sight distance and then factors in slope, wind speed, wind gusts, wind direction, temperature, and humidity to calculate a true “Plays Like” yardage. Instead of just getting raw distance, you receive the correct golf yardage based on real-time course conditions.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_Xzd3JJ": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do I need an Arccos game-tracking membership to use the Smart Laser?",
            "text": "<p>No. The Arccos Smart Laser is a standalone golf laser rangefinder and works independently without a game-tracking membership.</p><p>You can add Arccos game tracking at any time, but it is not required to use the device.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_mBKjNB": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What happens if I lose or damage my Smart Laser?",
            "text": "<p>If your Smart Laser Rangefinder is lost or damaged, you can purchase a replacement device for a one-time fee. Your Arccos subscription remains active and stays connected to your account.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_rXdYVi": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How is the Arccos Smart Laser different from a standard rangefinder with slope?",
            "text": "<p>Most golf rangefinders only account for slope-adjusted distance. The Arccos Smart Laser goes beyond slope by also adjusting for wind speed, wind gusts, wind direction, temperature, and humidity to calculate a true “Plays Like” distance.</p><p>Rather than providing only a line-of-sight yardage, it delivers the right number based on the actual playing conditions.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_73aEUt": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is the Arccos Smart Laser legal for tournament play?",
            "text": "<p>Yes — when Tournament Mode is enabled.</p><p>The Smart Laser includes a conforming mode that disables slope and environmental adjustments, making it legal for tournament and competition play under the Rules of Golf.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_XzgjEX": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do professional golfers use the Arccos Smart Laser?",
            "text": "<p>Yes. Major Champion Matt Fitzpatrick uses the Arccos Smart Laser and Arccos game-tracking data to refine strategy and dial in precise yardages.</p><p>Tour players rely on accurate distance and data-driven insights — and that’s exactly what the Smart Laser is built to deliver.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_Udbx3p": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Why does the Arccos Smart Laser require a subscription?",
            "text": "<p>Unlike traditional golf rangefinders, the Arccos Smart Laser operates on continuously evolving software, allowing it to improve over time.</p><p>Your subscription keeps your device updated with:</p><ul><li>AI Strategy recommendations<br/></li><li>Green Maps (where available)<br/></li><li>Live weather-adjusted yardages<br/></li><li>Ongoing software enhancements<br/></li></ul><p>It’s more than just a golf laser rangefinder — it’s a performance platform designed to get smarter after purchase.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
      },
